title: Tim and Jeff Buckley JJJ Radio Special 1996
description:
This is a recording of a special JJJ Radio in Australia ran on the evening of 29th March 1996. I originally recorded it onto to cassette then onto CD at that time. The 3 CD set has been at my brother&#039;s home while I roamed SE Asia and got into all sorts of trouble. It was the evening before Jeff&#039;s last ever concert with the band with Mick, Mike and Matt. I attended the unlisted concert at Selinas on the 1st March 1996 and it was excellent running for over 3 hours as I remember. I thank Andrew for his DAT to CD of that concert but it has been lost. The scanned photos are from the T-shirt I still own as a gift from Christine in Canberra. You are both fondly remembered. As this was a once-off event, I have recorded it at 320Kbits and the original taping is in good stead considering the 2 transcriptions.

Hopefully, this will be fully available as a bittorrent on the 12th anniversary of that now famous concert at Selinas. I had the pleasure to see Jeff at his first concert in Australia at The Metro, The Phoenician Club a week later in 1995. In 1996 I saw Jeff at the Enmore Theatre and Selinas. At The Phoenician and Selinas, I was about 2 metres from Jeff. On some recordings, my voice can be heard interjecting.

Lorn of Cambodia
